Levels of understanding

There are four stages of understanding of the concept of TidyTuesday:

  1. Ignoring it.
  2. Partially ignoring it, but slowly getting why it's on Tuesday.
  3. Finally getting it and being like .
  4. Participate.

The good news is, that transitioning from 1 - 4 is super easy by design!

R4DS community

R4DS = R for Data Science Online Learning Community

Goal: creating a supportive and responsive online space for learners and mentors to gather and work through the R for Data Science text

  • R4DS community: http://www.rfordatasci.com/ initiated by Jesse Maegan (@kierisi on twitter)
  • R4DS is a book: http://r4ds.had.co.nz/ (free online book)
  • R4DS community works through Blog + Twitter + Slack
  • TidyTuesday is part of this initiative

Tidyverse ecosystem

library(tidyverse)
## Base functions have analogous functions in the tidyverse.

What is #TidyTuesday?

A weekly data wrangling & visualisation project

Github repo

Details

  • Founded by Jesse Maegan and Thomas Mock
  • Started in April 2018
  • addresses the need of learning the tidyverse ecosystem by separating the technical and the interpretation part of DS.
  • Tamed, bot not tidy datasets along with some kind of template (articles)

How does #TidyTuesday work?

  • Data is released on Monday
  • Wrangle & visualise on Tuesday
  • publish results + code on twitter (#TidyTuesday)

How to participate in TidyTuesday

Datasets: the gold mine!

A variety of types of data!

The principle: Data + Publication

+

=

What are the possibilities?

  • Playing with data: data wrangling (tidying) + visualisation. Practicing the core skillset that helps us to do DS.
  • This combination of data + published figures allows you to explore tidyverse on different levels: reproduce something or create something new
  • having a community: learn from others
  • addresses the lack of new data at work (without having to think about implications).
  • It is like homework that you won't get checked on .
